  "text": "The magnesium dataset is unusual (see e.g. [CITATION_1] and is included simply to satisfy curiosity as to how the trimming method would deal with it. The very large ISIS-4 trial shows no treatment effect, but several small studies do show one; there is now believed to be little or no treatment effect. Fixed and random effect models give very different answers, and the random effect model gives the 'wrong' answer. Here, the smaller bagged mean and larger standard error already show a reduction in the effect (p = 0.044), but trimming removes much of the small studies, and gives a result similar to the (correct) fixed-effects model,θ = 0.0166 ± 0.035. This result may be fortuitous, but is perhaps encouraging.",
